sentences: Gillebert (Guillebert) de Berneville (fl. c.  1250–70) was a French trouvère.

Gillebert appears in the necrology of the jongleurs and bourgeois of Arras as being celebrated in a mass at Pentecost 1270, so he must have died between this commemorative mass and the previous one (i.e. some time between 2 Feb and 1 June 1270).
